Date:  0/5/1930
Source:  National Education
Author:
Vol / Page:  197
Edition:
Quote:  i was standing in a public hall in Wellington one evening, when i heard one young fellow ask another to `give him a knockdown to that tart in the green skirt'. i gathered that he was asking for an introduction to a young lady.
Notes:  (C.J. Hickson)

