Author:
Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Knock Down.</i> - (1) introduction: "He gave me a knock down to his sister.' (C.) (2) Spend (wages) lavishly or quickly, usually on drink. (Canterbury Rhymes, p. 12)
